      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779472001311,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Rate\nLimiter",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "NYN2-lKKqroIq5g3XBgyk",
      "originalText": "Rate Limiter",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Bfn0mI_o4qh9Wf34IQEeR",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1664.38671875,
      "y": 862.63671875,
      "width": 461.54547119140636,
      "height": 789.5366198942129,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aB",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 258972444,
      "version": 1870,
      "versionNonce": 382909980,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779473542558,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Rate limiting algorithms\n1. Fixed window counter\n    - N request per window\n    - if req > N, we reject\n    - Upside \n        - Uses hashtable\n    - Downside\n        - boundary effect\n        - starvation \n\n2. Sliding window log -> Smooth window within\nwindow\n- Upside\n    - eliminate boundary effect\n- Downside\n    - Memory intensive since it uses heap\n    - Expensive at scale and will require more\ninstances\n\n3. Sliding window counter\n    - Estimation via computed windows\n    - Downside\n         - Approximation, assumes even spread\nrequests\n\n4. Token Bucket\n - token are added at steady rate\n - bucket size designed for throttling\n - refill rate for controlled usage\n    - Enables steady load\n    - Downside\n        - Sizing\n     -Upside: Easy to implement\n",
      "fontSize": 18.57733223280501,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Rate limiting algorithms\n1. Fixed window counter\n    - N request per window\n    - if req > N, we reject\n    - Upside \n        - Uses hashtable\n    - Downside\n        - boundary effect\n        - starvation \n\n2. Sliding window log -> Smooth window within window\n- Upside\n    - eliminate boundary effect\n- Downside\n    - Memory intensive since it uses heap\n    - Expensive at scale and will require more instances\n\n3. Sliding window counter\n    - Estimation via computed windows\n    - Downside\n         - Approximation, assumes even spread requests\n\n4. Token Bucket\n - token are added at steady rate\n - bucket size designed for throttling\n - refill rate for controlled usage\n    - Enables steady load\n    - Downside\n        - Sizing\n     -Upside: Easy to implement\n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ZQq86M2DEArtklBB37kKG",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1663.5546875,
      "y": 543.15234375,
      "width": 478.23968505859375,
      "height": 300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aC",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1574024356,
      "version": 552,
      "versionNonce": 336553628,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779473538771,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Externalise state\n\nProcess\n1. Request comes in\n2. Gateway \n    - fetches token and last refill time from redis\n    - redis HMGET alice:bucket tokens last_refill\n3. Update counts based on rate and last refill\n4. Respond pass or fail based on if tokens > 0\n5.  Update bucket status\n\nAvoid read-after-write -> lua scripting",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Externalise state\n\nProcess\n1. Request comes in\n2. Gateway \n    - fetches token and last refill time from redis\n    - redis HMGET alice:bucket tokens last_refill\n3. Update counts based on rate and last refill\n4. Respond pass or fail based on if tokens > 0\n5.  Update bucket status\n\nAvoid read-after-write -> lua scripting",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
